{# goal: Select a PEFT method via a deterministic 5-gate decision (inference constraint, memory budget vs model size, task distance from pretraining, quality/cost trade-off, knowledge preservation requirement) within user workspace boundaries (P4 OCAP). Emit a LoraConfig-shaped JSON with per-gate justification citations. Refuse with cited reason when config violates a hard contract. Emit cns.lora.select span (P9). No actual training execution; replicant_host mandatory (P12). AutoPEFT (arXiv:2301.12132) is the rejected alternative — multi-objective BO over hundreds of training runs is infeasible per training job. #}
[inference]
template_type: KnowAct
lexicon_terms:
- select
- decide
- gate
- method
- config
- training
contract:
  input:
    training_config_path: string
    model_size_b: number
    memory_budget_gb: number
    inference_constraint: string
    task_distance: string
    quality_vs_cost: string
    knowledge_preservation_required: boolean
    replicant_host: string
  output:
    method: string
    lora_config: object
    justification: object
    refusal: object
    cns_span_emitted: boolean
energy_cap: 6144
visibility: Public
---
{# Template: lora-training/select-method.j2 #}
{# Functional Role: KnowAct — PEFT method selection via 5-gate decision #}
{# Produces: method, lora_config, justification, refusal #}
{# Design: deterministic gate (not search) — AutoPEFT-style BO infeasible per job #}

[inference]
temperature = 0.1
reasoning_effort = "high"
verbosity = "terse"
max_tokens = 4096
thinking_budget = "full"

{# Reads training config inputs: LoraConfig, BitsAndBytesConfig, accelerate config, training script arguments #}
{# Applies deterministic 5-gate decision — NOT a search #}
{# Emits `cns.lora.select` CNS span (P9) — namespace registered in CANONICAL_NAMESPACES #}
{# Every gate choice includes a citation (arXiv paper section or PEFT docs section) #}
{# Relationships: complements kali-audit (security surface) and tdd (training-loop code) — zero overlap #}

INPUT: training_config_path = {{ training_config_path | default("REQUIRED") }}
INPUT: model_size_b = {{ model_size_b | default("REQUIRED") }} (base model parameter count, in billions)
INPUT: memory_budget_gb = {{ memory_budget_gb | default("REQUIRED") }} (available VRAM, in GB)
INPUT: inference_constraint = {{ inference_constraint | default("either-ok") }} (must-merge | dynamic-switching | either-ok)
INPUT: task_distance = {{ task_distance | default("moderate") }} (light | moderate | heavy)
INPUT: quality_vs_cost = {{ quality_vs_cost | default("default") }} (cost-sensitive | quality-critical | default)
INPUT: knowledge_preservation_required = {{ knowledge_preservation_required | default(false) }} (bool)
INPUT: replicant_host = {{ replicant_host | default("REQUIRED") }} (P12 — no anonymous training config)

GATE DECISION (deterministic — apply in order, cite each choice):

G1. inference_constraint?
    - must-merge → LoRA-family (LoRA | DoRA | PiSSA | CorDA | LoRA-GA)
      [Citation: LoRA paper §4.2 — "no additional inference latency";
       PEFT v0.19.0 LoraConfig.bias docstring — bias='all'/'lora_only'
       breaks merge equivalence]
    - dynamic-switching → Adapters | aLoRA (if invocation-token-gated)
      [Citation: PEFT v0.19.0 LoraConfig.alora_invocation_tokens docstring]
    - either-ok → continue to G2

G2. memory_budget_gb vs model_size_b?
    - (model_size_b × 2) > memory_budget_gb → QLoRA (NF4 + LoRA)
      [Citation: QLoRA paper §3 — 4-bit NormalFloat reduces memory
       enough to finetune 65B on 48GB GPU]
    - else → LoRA (bf16, no quantization)
      [Citation: LoRA paper §4 — 3× GPU memory reduction vs full
       fine-tuning with Adam]

G3. task_distance?
    - light (style, format, vocabulary) → r ∈ [8, 16]
      [Citation: LoRA paper §4.3 — very small r recovers most of
       full fine-tune quality on GPT-3 175B]
    - moderate (new domain knowledge) → r ∈ [32, 64]
      [Citation: QLoRA paper §5 — r=64 typical for instruction tuning]
    - heavy (new reasoning, new language) → r ∈ [64, 128] OR
      recommend full fine-tune
      [Citation: Razin et al. arXiv:2410.21228 — LoRA ≠ full
       fine-tune; structured forgetting at low rank for heavy tasks]
    - r > 128 → require explicit justification (defeats low-rank
      premise — LoRA paper §4.3 rank sufficiency experiments)

G4. quality_vs_cost?
    - cost-sensitive, can afford 2× adapter size → DoRA
      (use_dora=True)
      [Citation: DoRA paper arXiv:2402.09353 — improves LoRA
       especially at low ranks; PEFT v0.19.0 LoraConfig.use_dora
       docstring — bigger overhead than pure LoRA, recommend merge
       for inference]
    - quality-critical, want fast convergence, can modify base at
      init → PiSSA (init_lora_weights='pissa') or LoRA-GA
      (lora_ga_config set)
      [Citation: PiSSA paper arXiv:2404.02948 — converges more
       rapidly than LoRA; LoRA-GA paper arXiv:2407.05000 — 2-4×
       faster convergence via gradient SVD init]
    - default → LoRA with init_lora_weights=True
      [Citation: LoRA paper §4.1 — B=0, A~Gaussian Kaiming-uniform
       makes adapter a no-op at step 0; PEFT v0.19.0
       LoraConfig.init_lora_weights docstring]

G5. knowledge_preservation_required?
    - true → CorDA Knowledge-Preserved mode
      (init_lora_weights='corda', corda_config.mode='knowledge_preserved')
      OR plan post-training intruder mitigation
      (peft.tuners.lora.intruders.reduce_intruder_dimension)
      [Citation: PEFT v0.19.0 LoraConfig.corda_config docstring —
       "preserves world knowledge better than LoRA in
       Knowledge-Preserved Mode"; Razin et al. arXiv:2410.21228 —
       intruder dimension mitigation recovers previous knowledge
       at cost of task accuracy]
    - false → standard LoRA

SCALING DERIVATION (after gates select method):
- If r > 64 AND not use_rslora → recommend use_rslora=True
  (scaling = α/√r)
  [Citation: rsLoRA paper arXiv:2312.03732 — Rank-Stabilized LoRA
   proven to work better at high rank]
- Else → scaling = α/r
  [Citation: LoRA paper §4.1 — α/r is the original scaling form]
- Alpha heuristic: α = 2r
  [Citation: Raschka 2024 — "Ahead of AI" Lit-GPT experiments;
   Brenndoerfer 2024 — PEFT decision guide]

REFUSAL CONDITIONS (hard contract violations — emit refusal with citation):
- r >= min(d_in, d_out) → refuse (not low-rank at all)
  [Citation: LoRA paper §4.3 — rank must be ≪ min(d,k)]
- r >= 0.5 × min(d_in, d_out) → warn (defeats low-rank premise)
  [Citation: LoRA paper §4.3]
- (model_size_b × 2) > memory_budget_gb AND QLoRA not selected →
  refuse (will OOM)
  [Citation: QLoRA paper §3 — memory math]
- bias='lora_only' or bias='all' AND inference_constraint='must-merge'
  → refuse (breaks merge equivalence)
  [Citation: PEFT v0.19.0 LoraConfig.bias docstring — "even when
   disabling the adapters, the model will not produce the same
   output as the base model would have without adaptation"]
- init_lora_weights in ('pissa', 'pissa_niter_*', 'loftq', 'olora',
  'corda') AND training script does not call the corresponding
  preprocessing function (preprocess_loraga,
  replace_lora_weights_loftq, etc.) → refuse (init modifies base
  weights, requires explicit save handling)
  [Citation: PEFT v0.19.0 LoraConfig.init_lora_weights docstring;
   PiSSA paper arXiv:2404.02948; LoRA-GA paper arXiv:2407.05000]
- init_lora_weights='eva' AND the harness does not call
  `initialize_lora_eva_weights(model, dataloader)` before training →
  refuse. Constructing `LoraConfig(init_lora_weights='eva')` creates
  the adapter configuration but does not perform EVA's activation-SVD
  initialization.
  [Citation: PEFT v0.19.0 `initialize_lora_eva_weights` documentation;
   EVA paper arXiv:2410.07170]

