CNS SPAN EMISSION (P9 — every training-config selection):
- `cns.lora.select` span: target `"cns.lora.select"`, message `"CNS"`,
  operation `"select_method"`, gate_inputs: {...}, selected_method,
  refusal_reason (if any), justification_citations, replicant_host,
  latency_ms.
- Namespace registered in `CANONICAL_NAMESPACES`
  (`crates/hkask-types/src/event.rs`). Emit unconditionally.

CONSTRAINTS (P5 minimalism, P8 evidence integrity, P12 host):
- No synthetic config values. Every gate choice must cite a concrete
  source (arXiv paper section, PEFT v0.19.0 docstring section).
- No actual training execution (P4 boundary — config selection only).
- No model download; reads declared workspace config paths only.
- Every selection action includes `replicant_host` identity (P12).
- Registry (`manifest.yaml` + `.j2`) authoritative over SKILL.md (P5.1).
- Do NOT use AutoPEFT-style search (arXiv:2301.12132) — multi-objective
  BO over hundreds of training runs is infeasible per training job.
  Use deterministic gate instead. Cite AutoPEFT as the rejected
  alternative.
- Do NOT recommend AdaLoRA (arXiv:2303.10512) as a default — overhead
  and instability outweigh marginal gains for domain-specific
  fine-tuning (per RaLo, ScienceDirect 2025). Allow only when user
  explicitly requests dynamic rank allocation.
- Do NOT recommend Prefix Tuning for production — latency cost not
  worth marginal parameter savings (per Brenndoerfer 2024, Spheron
  2026 PEFT decision guides).
- When conflicting with `kali-audit` findings, `kali-audit` covers
  security surface; this skill covers training config — they are
  complementary, not overlapping.
- When conflicting with `tdd`, `tdd` covers training-loop code
  correctness; this skill governs the config the loop consumes.

5W1H GATE (P5 — minimal):
- Who: Training operator / replicant host (P12).
- What: PEFT method selection / LoraConfig / training hyperparameters.
- Where: Training script / config file / model card.
- When: Pre-training gate (before launching training job).
- Why: P3.1 safe container (training-config errors silently degrade
  model quality) / P1 user sovereignty over training choices / P4
  explicit training boundaries.
- How: Read config inputs → apply 5 gates → derive scaling → emit
  LoraConfig JSON with justification → emit CNS span → refuse if
  hard contract violated.
All 6 present — passes gate.

